Which of the following is/ are the part of operating system?
A) Kernel services
B) Library services
C) Application level services
D) All of the above
D) All of the above
ANS-D) All of the above

The system of ............... generally ran one job at a time. These were called single stream batch
processing.
A) 40's
B) 50's
C) 60's
D) 70's
ANS-B) 50's

In ............. generation of operating system, operating system designers develop the concept of
multiprogramming in which several jobs are in main memory at once.
A) First
B) Second
C) Third
D) Fourth
ANS-C) Third

State True or False.
i) In spooling high speed device like a disk is interposed between running program and low-speed device
in Input/output.
ii) By using spooling for example instead of writing directly to a printer, outputs are written to the disk.
A) i-True, ii-False
B) i-True, ii-True
C) i-False, ii-True
D) i-False, ii-False
ANS-B) i-True, ii-True

Which of the following is/are the functions of operating system?
i) Sharing hardware among users. ii) Allowing users to share data among themselves.
iii) Recovering from errors. iv) Preventing users from interfering with one another.
v) Scheduling resources among users.
A) i, ii, iii and iv only
B) ii, iii, iv and v only
C) i, iii, iv and v only
D) All i, ii, iii, iv and v
ANS-D) All i, ii, iii, iv and v

.................. executes must frequently and makes the fine grained decision of which process to
execute the next.
A) Long-term scheduling
B) Medium-term scheduling
C) Short-term scheduling
D) None of the above
ANS-C) Short-term scheduling

With ................ a page is brought into main memory only when the reference is made to a location
on that page.
A) demand paging
B) main paging
C) prepaging
D) postpaging
ANS-A) demand paging
....................... provides a larger sized of virtual memory but require virtual memory which provides
multidimensional memory.
A) Paging method
B) Segmentation method
C) Paging and segmentation method
D) None of these
ANS-B) Segmentation method

............... is a large kernel containing virtually the complete operating system, including,
scheduling, file system, device drivers and memory management.
A) Multilithic kernel
B) Monolithic kernel
C) Micro kernel
D) Macro kernel
ANS-B) Monolithic kernel

............... is a large operating system core provides a wide range of services.
A) Multilithic kernel
B) Monolithic kernel
C) Micro kernel
D) Macro kernel
ANS-D) Macro kernel

Which of the following is not the function of Microkernel?
A) File management
B) Low-level memory management
C) Inter-process communication
D) I/O interrupts management
ANS-A) File management

Match the following.
i) Mutual exclusion a) A process may hold allocated resources while waiting assignment.
ii) Hold and wait b) No resource can be forcibly removed from a process holding it.
iii) No preemption c) Only one process may use a resource at a time.
A) i-a, ii-b, iii-c
B) i-a, ii-c, iii-b
C) i-b, ii-c, iii-a
D) i-c, ii-a, iii-b
ANS-D) i-c, ii-a, iii-b

A direct method of deadlock prevention is to prevent the occurrences of ...................
A) Mutual exclusion
B) Hold and wait
C) Circular waits
D) No preemption
ANS-C) Circular waits

The methods or algorithms which are used to increase the performance of disk storage sub-system
is called .............
A) Disk performing
B) Disk scheduling
C) Disk storing
D) Disk extending
ANS-B) Disk scheduling

................. is the time required to move the disk arm to the required track.
A) Seek time
B) Rotational delay
C) Latency time
D) Access time
ANS-A) Seek time

The ............... policy restricts scanning to one direction only.
A) SCAN
B) C-SCAN
C) N-Step SCAN
D) Both A and B
ANS-A) SCAN

............... policy selects the disk I/O request that requires the least movement of the disk arm
from its current position.
A) FSCAN
B) SSTF
C) SCAN
D) C-SCAN
ANS-B) SSTF

.................. refers to the ability of an operating system to support multiple threads of execution
with a single process.
A) Multithreading
B) Multiprocessing
C) Multiexecuting
D) Bi-threading
ANS-A) Multithreading

State whether the following statement is true.
i) It takes less time to terminate a thread than a process.
ii) Threads enhance efficiency in communication between different executing programs.
A) i-True, ii-False
B) i-True, ii-True
C) i-False, ii-True
D) i-False, ii-False
ANS-B) i-True, ii-True

............ is a special type of programming language used to provide instructions to the monitor
simple batch processing schema.
A) Job control language (JCL)
B) Processing control language (PCL)
C) Batch control language (BCL)
D) Monitor control language (MCL)
ANS-A) Job control language (JCL)

1. What is an Operating System? 
a) Software that manages hardware resources
b) Hardware that executes software
c) A language for programming
d) None of the above
Answer: a) Software that manages hardware resources

2. Which of the following is NOT a function of an OS?
a) Memory management 
b) Process scheduling 
c) Compiling code 
d) File system management
Answer: c) Compiling code

3. Which part of the OS runs continuously?
a) Kernel
b) Application software 
c) Device drivers 
d) GUI
Answer: a) Kernel

4. Which type of software is an operating system? 
a) System software 
b) Application software 
c) Utility software 
d) None of the above
Answer: a) System software

5. What is the main function of an OS? 
a) Manage computer resources 
b) Execute user applications 
c) Provide an interface to the user 
d) All of the above 
Answer: d) All of the above

6. Which OS type processes jobs in a sequential manner?
a) Real-Time OS 
b) Time-Sharing OS 
c) Batch OS
d) Distributed OS 
Answer: c) Batch OS

7. Which OS type allows multiple users to access the system at the same time? 
a) Single-user OS 
b) Time-sharing OS 
c) Embedded OS 
d) None of the above 
Answer: b) Time-sharing OS

8. Which OS is used for real-time applications? 
a) Windows 
b) Linux 
c) RTOS 
d) MacOS 
Answer: c) RTOS

9. Which OS can be found in smartphones? 
a) Unix b) Windows Server c) Android d) Fedora
Answer: c) Android

10. Which OS type controls multiple computers connected in a network? 
a) Network OS b) Real-Time OS c) Embedded OS d) Batch OS 
Answer: a) Network OS

11. Which memory management technique divides memory into fixed sizes? 
a) Segmentation b) Paging c) Contiguous allocation d) Swapping 
Answer: b) Paging

12. What is the role of virtual memory? 
a) Increase cache size b) Provide additional RAM using secondary storage c) Improve processor speed d) Manage user access
Answer: b) Provide additional RAM using secondary storage

13. Which memory allocation technique allows variable-sized memory blocks? 
a) Paging b) Segmentation c) Fixed partitioning d) Fragmentation
Answer: b) Segmentation

14. What type of fragmentation occurs in paging?
a) Internal b) External c) Both d) None
Answer: a) Internal

15. Which algorithm selects the oldest page for replacement?
a) LRU b) FIFO c) Optimal d) Random 
Answer: b) FIFO



